[2] Cholera - Angola - Huambo
Date: Mon, 18 Dec 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=495542>

Cholera that has so far killed 20 persons out of 177 recorded from 24
Nov to 17 Dec 2006 in Angola's central Huambo province, continues
spreading into other provincial capital city's surrounding compounds.
According to the spokesperson for Huambo`s provincial department of
health, Isaac Kassenge, the disease has reached the compounds of
Benfica, Canhe, Cacilhas, Centro and Calomanda. The disease had
earlier on been confined to the compounds of Macolocolo, Calilongue
da Cuca, Chiva and Bom Pastor, all on the outskirts of Huambo city.
The source who would not add figures, said the cases of the disease
that started from Macolocolo is killing mainly adults.
"We continue appealing to the population to put into practice the
measures of prevention of cholera. All must abide by the advices in
order for the disease to be brought under control," said Isaac
Kassenge.
Church and traditional authorities, as well as activists and partners
of the health sector in Huambo are working hard in awareness
campaigns in the compounds affected, seeking to control the disease.
Tents to isolate cholera patients have been purchased by the health
services to improve their treatment. They will be erected near the
central hospital and the Benguela Railways (CFB), on the outskirts of
Huambo city.
--
