[3] Cholera - Angola (Benguela)
Date: Thu, 21 Dec 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=496285>

At least 11 people have died, all victims of cholera, out of 131
cases notified by Ganda municipal hospital, coastal Benguela province
since 6 Dec 2006.
Angop has learnt that about 42 patients are still in the hospital.
The local authorities are worried about this situation and 5 working
commissions have been created in the affected communities to educate
and sensitize the population on first aid and basic sanitary measures
to stop the spreading of the disease in the region.
