[5] Cholera - Tanzania (Rukwa)
Date: Wed, 20 Dec 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Daily News Tanzania [edited]
<http://www.dailynews-tsn.com/page.php?id=4952>

A 35-year-old from Majengo at Kashaulili Ward in Mpanda District,
Rukwa Region, died following the outbreak of cholera in the area,
where 45 people were admitted to health centers between 5 Nov and 17
Dec 2006, an official said.
Acting Mpanda District Medical Officer (DMO), Dr Andrew Kapaya, told
the 'Daily News' that some of those admitted were released after
clinical tests proved that they were not suffering from cholera. He
said the victims were in bad shape after excessive vomiting and
purging.
The DMO said man died on 28 Nov 2006. Dr Kapaya said from 30 Nov to
17 Dec, the center admitted 26 patients who were proved to have
contracted cholera after clinical tests. He said all patients were
from Kashaulili.
The disease has frequently broken out in the past 3 decades in
various parts of the country, including Dar es Salaam and Zanzibar.
[Byline: Peti Siyame]
--
