[7] Cholera - Philippines (Camarines Sur)
Date: Tue, 19 Dec 2006
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org
Source: Philippine Daily Inquirer [edited]
<http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/inquirerheadlines/regions/view_article.php?article_id=39035>

Three cases of cholera have been confirmed by health authorities here
amid an outbreak of diarrhea that affected at least 70 persons in
Barangay Hamorawon of Minalabac. Dr. Flavel Florenda, municipal
health officer, confirmed on Mon, 17 Dec 2006, there were 3 cases of
cholera based on the result of laboratory tests conducted at the
Bicol Medical Center (BMC).
Florenda said they expect more data this week, from the Camarines Sur
provincial health team that went to the area in response to reports
of rising numbers of cases of diarrhea in Hamorawon. She said only 6
fecal swabs were collected from 6 different persons with symptoms of
cholera, which included the discharge of watery feces colored like
water used to rinse rice.
Florenda said the first reported victim died at the BMC the day
Supertyphoon Reming hit Camarines Sur.
--
